e beginning of a fight instead of doing maintenance heals after a fight? In a good group, this does not happen often.<br>
<br>
I have played a ranger to 60; and now my warrior is close to a similar level. Do you know how many times my ranger was passed over for groups because they needed a tank? I can't count the times really. For the first 6 months of Kunark, I could not buy a group because the perception was rangers were broken. Fact was, they had changed but were not broken, except for one thing.. ability to dump agro was needed. VI gave rangers jolt and rangers learned to manage their agro because their role had changed.<br>
<br>
Rangers also hurt themselves alot by whining. Word got around that rangers sucked, and it took about 6 months for that perception to change. If we, as warriors spread the word that we suck because one skill is broken, well we are hurting ourselves more than helping ourselves.<br>
<br>
Right now, as it stands, maybe the perfect group does not include warriors.. but warriors are interchangable. They can fill any melee slot, except a rogue. <br>
<br>
Do you think a group who wants to get started is going to wait for a SK or a Knight to come along, instead of just getting started? <br>
<br>
We have to have a paladin to have an exp group???? a cleric maybe, but a paladin or SK???? I think you are giving them to much credit.<br>
<br>
I have never seen a group say.. lets not fill this last slot with that warrior, lets wait on a rogue, ranger, or monk. Now I have heard them say lets wait on a shaman or chanter of course; because slow is needed so badly at higher levels.<br>
<br>
That being said, I just don't like the whining I have seen here. Other classes have endured just as much as warriors have, and even more. So its time to suck it up a bit. Stop whining, but instead provide a logical case as to why we need to be fixed.<br>
<br>
If you get passed over for a group because a paladin or SK is LFG at the same time as you, live with it, and don't whine. Because you are only propgating a false notion that warriors are completely broken, which they aren't. You would be hurting your own ability to find a group in the long run.<br>
<br>
Instead lets provide Verant a way to fix the one thing wrong with warriors. Taunt..<br>
<br>
If there is anything that needs to be fixed with warriors, its the ability to taunt. To fix it, an AA that allows the taunt cap to be raised to to 300 max, and another AA that allows taunt to refresh faster would work. Also a new mega taunt would work, one that would hit every time its used (a taunt like a lure so to speak), but lets say only refreshes every 3 minutes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lets help ourselves instead of hurting ourselves here..<br>
<br>
 <p>-Pin<br>
