<br>
You could argue that if everything is going well that a druid can bring more to the table then a cleric with the use of snare/harmony and better nukers/dot (similar to saying that a warrior will do more dps then a paladin or provide better tanking).  But when someone dies in your group and you have a druid, you wish you had gotten a cleric instead.<br>
<br>
In the overrall picture of class balance though, I think the warrior taunt issue is a pretty small one.  If you look at experience group, the disparity of enchanter, druids, some mages and necro using charm to aa xp is 100 times more broken then whatever disparity that could exist between tanks classes.  I've been rejected out of many more groups &quot;cause they were using charm pets to tanks and didnt need a pitifull melee doing 100dps with only 9k hp&quot; and I'm one of the uber warrior out there.  <br>
<br>
After that you have raid where warrior do not too bad cause mobs hit so hard, but where in some very important key fights most melee are forced to watch from far away looking at 1 ranger doing the combined dps of the 5 monks, the 3 rogues and the 3 warriors non mtanking.  This issue is more general I guess.<br>
<br>
If they eventually come around and look at things like paladin stuns maybe they will nerf them which will close the gap at aggro somewhat but there are things that plague melee that are much worse then that imo.<br>
