<br>
It is not the warriors job to keep aggro.  It is the slowers, stunners, nukers job to not get aggro.  it is the warriors job to take the damage.<br>
<br>
That being said, aggro will switch to the caster in some cases.  the ability of a pally to stun to get aggro back is a crutch that is overused by overnukers, nuking clerics, etc...<br>
<br>
If you wait for the warrior to get enough aggro, you wont grab aggro with a nuke.  warriors can withstand the onslaught until they do get enough aggro.<br>
<br>
IF a warrior get aggro, and the taunt hits, they have aggro.  its just how taunt works (lets not get into the debate) and problem solved.  if the taunt doesnt hit, a shammy can withstand the beating until either damage, a successful taunt, or a good proc will grab aggro back.<br>
<br>
Yes, pallies have the ability to get aggo quickly, BUT as i said, its a crutch, and if leaned on too much, the casters will get lazy, and :LOADING, PLEASE WAIT.<br>
